20/05/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Arsonists targeted five mosques in separate districts of Istanbul on Tuesday (May 19th), causing property damage but no injuries, authorities said.
The attacks targeted the Yildiz Mosque in the Tuzla district, the Gul and Sihli mosques in the Pendik district and two other mosques in other areas of Istanbul.
In December, police arrested a mentally ill person for 13 arson attacks on mosques in the city.
(CNNTurk, HaberTurk, RIA Novosti, AP - 19/05/09)
